<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 6:30AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>WEATHER...
* A burst of higher intensity snowfall will impact the Thumb
region through 8 AM this morning.
* Snowfall rates up to a half inch per hour will be possible with
this round of snow.
* Temperatures hovering around 32F combined with higher intensity
snowfall rates may allow snow to accumulate on roadways,
especially those left untreated.
IMPACTS...
* Drivers should be prepared for reduced visibilities and
variable road conditions during the morning commute.
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
